        "last_activity_date": 1643045694,
        "creation_date": 1299260072,
        "answer_count": 11,
        "title": "How to set the Default Value of a ListPreference",
        "body": "<p>i need to set the defult value for a ListPreference when the Activity starts.\nI've tried with <code>ListPreference.setDefaultvalue(\"value\");<\/code> but it makes the firts Entry of the List as default. I need it because i must check a condition and set as default the value which satisfies that condition, so I think it can't be done from the xml file (with <code>android:defaultValue<\/code>)<\/p>\n\n<p>For example, suppose I have this array of values in the arrays.xml:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;string-array name=\"opts\"&gt;\n    &lt;item&gt;red&lt;/item&gt;\n    &lt;item&gt;green&lt;/item&gt;\n    &lt;item&gt;blue&lt;/item&gt;\n&lt;/string-array&gt;\n\n&lt;string-array name=\"opts_values\"&gt;\n    &lt;item&gt;1&lt;/item&gt;\n    &lt;item&gt;2&lt;/item&gt;\n    &lt;item&gt;3&lt;/item&gt;\n&lt;/string-array&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>In the PreferenceScreen xml:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;ListPreference\n    android:title=\"Colour select\"\n    android:summary=\"Select your favourite\"\n    android:key=\"colour\"\n    android:entries=\"@array/opts\"\n    android:entryValues=\"@array/opts_values\" /&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>In the Activity I'd like to do something like this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>String mycolour;\nif (something) {\n    mycolour=\"1\";\n} else {\n    mycolour=\"2\";\n}\nListPreference colour = (ListPreference) findPreference (\"colour\");\ncolour.setDefaultValue(mycolour);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>But it doesn't work, because it makes the first choice as default. Could you explain me how to make another one as default? Thanks.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 5197228,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "android",
            "android-preferences",
            "preference",
            "listpreference"
        ],
        "score": 62,
        "accepted_answer_id": 5197394,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 56887,
        "last_edit_date": 1402794095
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/GEnPS.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 1136185,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1121225,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1121225/md-naushad-alam",
                "reputation": 8611,
                "display_name": "Md. Naushad Alam",
                "accept_rate": 62
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 115,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1598734694,
            "creation_date": 1373170364,
            "body": "<p>You don't need to programmatically handle the default value of <code>ListPreferences<\/code>. You can do this in xml setting file. Below is an example<\/p>\n<pre><code>&lt;string-array name=&quot;opts&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;item&gt;red&lt;/item&gt;\n    &lt;item&gt;green&lt;/item&gt;\n    &lt;item&gt;blue&lt;/item&gt;\n&lt;/string-array&gt;\n\n&lt;string-array name=&quot;opts_values&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;item&gt;1&lt;/item&gt;\n    &lt;item&gt;2&lt;/item&gt;\n    &lt;item&gt;3&lt;/item&gt;\n&lt;/string-array&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>...<\/p>\n<pre><code>&lt;ListPreference\n    android:title=&quot;Colour select&quot;\n    android:summary=&quot;Select your favourite&quot;\n    android:key=&quot;colour&quot;\n    android:entries=&quot;@array/opts&quot;\n    android:entryValues=&quot;@array/opts_values&quot;\n    android:defaultValue=&quot;2&quot; /&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>here I selected <code>2<\/code> as a default value. Remember <code>defaultvalue<\/code> will be <code>opts_values<\/code> element.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 17509197,
            "question_id": 5197228,
            "last_edit_date": 1598734694
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/17f219cd389730e9fd42cc3dbfd776d3?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 319665,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 637545,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/637545/biddulph-r",
                "reputation": 5266,
                "display_name": "biddulph.r"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 28,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1299261013,
            "creation_date": 1299261013,
            "body": "<p>Have you tried: <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>setValueIndex(int index);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 5197394,
            "question_id": 5197228
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/7be63c3e6256a38f8644c81f5fde1217?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 3693714,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 3075692,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3075692/leandro-p",
                "reputation": 185,
                "display_name": "Leandro P."
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 13,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1391725202,
            "creation_date": 1391725202,
            "body": "<p>Sorry my bad English. <\/p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>List item<\/li>\n<li>Retrieve the list Check if the value is null. If it is null set to the default value.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n<p><strong>Code:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>ListPreference dataPref = (ListPreference) findPreference(\"keyList\");\n\nif(dataPref.getValue() == null){\n    dataPref.setValueIndex(0); //set to index of your deafult value\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 21615308,
            "question_id": 5197228
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://graph.facebook.com/100005606403833/picture?type=large",
                "account_id": 3730291,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 3102913,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3102913/pavel",
                "reputation": 1700,
                "display_name": "pavel",
                "accept_rate": 33
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 6,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1503499934,
            "creation_date": 1503499934,
            "body": "<p>You can set your default value by using the key like this <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;string-array name=\"syncFrequency\"&gt;\n    &lt;item name=\"1\"&gt;Block All Calls&lt;/item&gt;\n    &lt;item name=\"2\"&gt;Block Black List&lt;/item&gt;\n    &lt;item name=\"3\"&gt;Block Unknown Calls&lt;/item&gt;\n    &lt;item name=\"4\"&gt;Allow White List&lt;/item&gt;\n    &lt;item name=\"5\"&gt;Receive All Calls&lt;/item&gt;\n&lt;/string-array&gt;\n\n\n\n\n&lt;string-array name=\"syncFrequencyValues\"&gt;\n    &lt;item name=\"1\"&gt;Block_All_Calls&lt;/item&gt;\n    &lt;item name=\"2\"&gt;Block_Black_List&lt;/item&gt;\n    &lt;item name=\"3\"&gt;Block_Unknown_Calls&lt;/item&gt;\n    &lt;item name=\"4\"&gt;Allow_White_List&lt;/item&gt;\n    &lt;item name=\"5\"&gt;Receive_All_Calls&lt;/item&gt;\n&lt;/string-array&gt;\n\n\n\n     &lt;ListPreference\n        android:key=\"prefSyncFrequency\"\n        android:entries=\"@array/syncFrequency\"\n        android:summary=\"%s\"\n        android:defaultValue=\"Block_Black_List\"\n        android:entryValues=\"@array/syncFrequencyValues\"\n        android:title=\"@string/call_block_options\" /&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 45843083,
            "question_id": 5197228
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fa0eb06f9ab072dc55b70e37d3c560f3?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 198647,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 443427,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/443427/ungalcrys",
                "reputation": 5748,
                "display_name": "ungalcrys"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 3,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1334080754,
            "creation_date": 1334053747,
            "body": "<p>or you can also try <code>colour.setValue(mycolour);<\/code><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 10087028,
            "question_id": 5197228,
            "last_edit_date": 1334080754
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/rqccT.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 1534683,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1431044,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1431044/langusten-gustel",
                "reputation": 11012,
                "display_name": "Langusten Gustel",
                "accept_rate": 92
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 3,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1409560492,
            "creation_date": 1374760922,
            "body": "<p><strong>Just for the record if someone else has this problem:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<p><code>setValueIndex(int X)<\/code> is setting the value @ index X to the default value - so <strong>it is <em>probably<\/em> what you  are looking for<\/strong>. <\/p>\n\n<p>Set this value <strong>AFTER<\/strong> you added the Values! <em>(stupid mistake but took me half an hour)<\/em><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 17860196,
            "question_id": 5197228,
            "last_edit_date": 1409560492
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/793482f65f9c5368783dbdd35d4b0651?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 1666848,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1534073,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1534073/laomo",
                "reputation": 436,
                "display_name": "laomo"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 3,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1504777748,
            "creation_date": 1416303521,
            "body": "<pre><code>((ListPreference) findPreference(\"pref_language\")).setValue(Locale\n                .getDefault().getLanguage());\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p><code>setValue()<\/code> is ListPreference's method, and <code>setDefaultvalue<\/code> is Preference's method<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 26990978,
            "question_id": 5197228,
            "last_edit_date": 1504777748
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/6f97b5a189356c89aeaa159d5c6794c6?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 9160665,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 6812084,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6812084/yijun-li",
                "reputation": 57,
                "display_name": "Yijun Li"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 3,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1473404162,
            "creation_date": 1473398697,
            "body": "<p>Actually it's because the SharedPreferences will persist after you re-build the app.\nUninstall it and try again.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 39404379,
            "question_id": 5197228,
            "last_edit_date": 1473404162
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/kEmAOp9b.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 7763952,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 5875726,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5875726/wooldridgetm",
                "reputation": 2530,
                "display_name": "wooldridgetm"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 2,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1489190979,
            "creation_date": 1489190979,
            "body": "<p>This is an old post, but here's another way to set the default value for <code>ListPreference<\/code> with the following line of code:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>PreferenceManager.setDefaultValues(getActivity(), R.xml.preferences, false);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 42729780,
            "question_id": 5197228
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ba1627f54e3b9c1d5f1ecb27b44b0b07?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 430875,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 814548,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/814548/vivek",
                "reputation": 13598,
                "display_name": "Vivek",
                "accept_rate": 58
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 2,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1541566290,
            "creation_date": 1541566290,
            "body": "<p>Use the xml attribute <code>android:defaultValue=\"&lt;VALUE&gt;\"<\/code> in your list tag to set the default value.<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Note: the <code>&lt;VALUE&gt;<\/code> is the actual value and not the index of string\n  array.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>If still its not working, try below steps.<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Clear application data.<\/li>\n<li>Uninstall and reinstall the app<\/li>\n<li>Check the list preference, you will see the default value selected<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p>Strange, I know but it worked in my case.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 53183724,
            "question_id": 5197228
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/---U_0Y73QRU/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/ACHi3rf0LzttTMyxLaZqQGH76JqpdGcwMQ/mo/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
                "account_id": 15944534,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 11505496,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/11505496/fernando-campa%c3%b1a",
                "reputation": 1,
                "display_name": "Fernando Campa&#241;a"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1643045694,
            "creation_date": 1643045233,
            "body": "<p>If you are using Android Jetpack Preference, known as <code>androidx.preference:preference-ktx:1.1.1<\/code> in Kotlin, you can use:<\/p>\n<p><code>app:defaultValue=&quot;&lt;Value_in_string-array_with_values&gt;&quot;<\/code>.<\/p>\n<p>Additionally: <code>defaultValue<\/code> is not an index number, is the actual value from the values array.<\/p>\n<p>I also recommend using a string resource for the default value and <strong>clearing the data, uninstalling the app<\/strong>, or removing the file:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>&lt;package_name_in_app_manifest&gt;_preferences.xml<\/code> in <code>data/data/shared_prefs/&lt;package_name_in_app_manifest&gt;<\/code>. Replace <code>&lt;package_name_in_app_manifest&gt;<\/code> with real name like <code>com.example.yourapp<\/code>.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>I was having the same issue and the <code>defaultValue<\/code> wasn't updating because it already had a wrong default value of &quot;true&quot;. Solved it by using the Android Studio File Explorer and deleting the file.<\/p>\n<p>And here is my solution example:<\/p>\n<p><code>res/xml/root_preferences.xml<\/code><\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;ListPreference\u2028    \n    app:key=&quot;mic&quot;\u2028    \n    app:title=&quot;@string/select_mic_title&quot;\u2028 \n    app:useSimpleSummaryProvider=&quot;true&quot;\u2028   \n    app:entries=&quot;@array/mic_entries&quot;\u2028\n    app:entryValues=&quot;@array/mic_values&quot;\n    app:defaultValue=&quot;@string/default_mic&quot;\u2028    /&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p><code>res/values/arrays<\/code><\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;!-- Mic Preference --&gt;\u2028\n&lt;string-array name=&quot;mic_entries&quot;&gt;\u2028\n    &lt;item&gt;@string/default_mic&lt;/item&gt;\u2028\n    &lt;item&gt;Headband&lt;/item&gt;\u2028\n&lt;/string-array&gt;\u2028\u2028\n&lt;string-array name=&quot;mic_values&quot;&gt;\n\u2028    &lt;item&gt;@string/default_mic&lt;/item&gt;\u2028\n    &lt;item&gt;Headband&lt;/item&gt;\n\u2028&lt;/string-array&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p><code>res/strings.xml<\/code><\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;string name=&quot;default_mic&quot;&gt;Integrated&lt;/string&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>Result:\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/otihY.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Setting Fragment with default list value of &quot;Integrated&quot; given by string resource @string/default_mic<\/a><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 70837969,
            "question_id": 5197228,
            "last_edit_date": 1643045694
        }
    ],
